Britain will experience the first real taste of winter this week when freezing winds bring snow to much of the country.

Some of the coldest weather of the year is expected by Tuesday, with bitter blasts from the Arctic causing widespread frosts and plunging temperatures.

Wednesday night is expected to be the coldest since last winter. 

