By then, most parts of the country will have seen wintry showers and some high ground in the north will be shivering in temperatures as low as minus-three, with significant snowfalls.

According to the Met Office,  even cities such as Manchester and Leeds will experience temperatures as low as minus-two.

The meteorologists are also predicting light snow in parts of the South-West by Tuesday afternoon, and sleet over the Pennines on Wednesday afternoon.

